commText: Prabhsimran and Bairstow are at the crease. Prabhsimran is on strike. Santner will open the attack

Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, so nearly! A wicked inswinger - that shapes back in so late from outside off, Prabhsimran goes for a big drive and the ball stays near his feet after taking the thick inside-edge, for a moment he did not know where the ball was, Dhoni was ready to pounce
Santner to Prabhsimran, 1 run, tossed up full on off, Prabhsimran gets forward to push wide of cover, is off the mark
Santner to Bairstow, no run, flat good length and again hones in to middle-stump, Bairstow makes room and punches to cover
Santner to Bairstow, no run, slower and shorter outside off, extra bounce too, Bairstow cuts and misses, not far from the edge
Santner to Bairstow, 1 run, good length and curves back in to middle, Bairstow makes room and punches wide of cover
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, back of a length and angling into middle-stump, Prabhsimran knocks it to mid-on and retains the strike with that run

Designated wicketkeepers batting at No.9 or below in the IPL 6 times - Mahesh Rawat (RR, 2008-2009) Twice - Pinal Shah (MI, 2009) Once - Uday Kaul (PBKS, 2008) Once - Wriddhiman Saha (SRH, 2021) Once - MS Dhoni (CSK, 2024)
Tushar Deshpande, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Bairstow, wide, full and wide down leg, Bairstow flicks and misses, wide

Tushar Deshpande to Bairstow, FOUR, genuine chance and right between Dhoni and the wide slip. Fullish on off, Bairstow gets forward to drive, thick outside-edge flies to the right of Dhoni who had his weight to his left, he can barely move and definitely does not want to dive, well wide of the wide slip, runs away, Tushar Deshpande is a disappointed man

Tushar Deshpande to Bairstow, 2 runs, more luck for Bairstow, good length and nips back in from outside off, he gets forward to punch and a thick inside-edge misses off-stump and beats Dhoni to his left
Tushar Deshpande to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Tushar Deshpande to Bairstow, out Bowled!! Fine comeback this. A good length delivery that nips back in to the pads, Bairstow is beaten for pace, pushes and the ball misses the inside-edge to thud into the pad, deflects on to the off-stump. Tushar Deshpande is pumped. CSK have the dangerous Bairstow. Bairstow b Tushar Deshpande 7(6) [4s-1]
Rilee Rossouw, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Tushar Deshpande to Rossouw, no run, full just outside off, pushed to the left of cover
Tushar Deshpande to Rossouw, no run, fullish on off, pushed square with an open face to backward point
Tushar Deshpande to Rossouw, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Tushar Deshpande to Rossouw, out Bowled!! Knocked him over. The furniture is disturbed and Tushar Deshpande is thrilled. He is pumping his fists vigorously. A sharp length delivery that skids on, beats Rossouw for pace, who is late on the defence, the ball rushes past the bat to strike timber. Dream start for CSK this. Rossouw b Tushar Deshpande 0(3)
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, slower and shorter outside off, cut straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, flat good length and swerves back in, Prabhsimran defends it back
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, Prabhsimran makes room and Santner follows him with a length ball outside the leg-stump, punched to cover
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, the arm-ball and it comes back so late, Prabhsimran did well there actually, was deceived intially but cuts from off-stump to backward point
Santner to Prabhsimran, 1 run, good length and swerves into the pads, glanced to short fine-leg for one
Santner to Shashank Singh, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Shashank Singh gets forward to drive to long-off and he is off the mark
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, FOUR, what timing. Just a check loft that was. Full outside off, Shashank Singh did not go full pelt on the drive but it clears mid-off comfortably
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, no run, good length and outside off, Shashank Singh strides forward to defend it back

Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, no run, short of length outside off, holds its line with extra bounce, Shashank Singh punches on the rise and misses, ambitious shot with no feet and Shashank nearly edges it behind, shakes his head as he knows it was a bad shot
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, no run, beautiful outswinger, on a length and moving away from outside off, Shashank Singh again stands and wafts at it, well away from the body, beaten
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, 1 run, short of length and too straight on the stumps, turned through the vacant square leg area

Tushar Deshpande to Prabhsimran, no run, superb bowling. Tushar Deshpande is running in with great rhythm here, wide of the crease and the angle in takes it towards fourth-stump, then it holds its line to beat the push of Prabhsimran, very close to the outside-edge
Richard Gleeson, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Richard Gleeson to Shashank Singh, wide, short of length and down leg, Shashank Singh pulls and misses
Richard Gleeson to Shashank Singh, FOUR, Shashank Singh is on the charge, shimmies down and cuts the back of a length delivery outside off powerfully over point, flies away
Richard Gleeson to Shashank Singh, 1 run, hard back of a length outside off, nips back in a tad, Shashank Singh punches and it's off the thick inside half, down to mid-on for one
Richard Gleeson to Prabhsimran, SIX, Richard Gleeson has not started well, short of length and angling into the body, Prabhsimran swivels and pulls into the crowd at fine-leg, just flew off the bat
Richard Gleeson to Prabhsimran, 1 run, good length and on middle-stump, Prabhsimran defends in front of mid-wicket and it's an easy single

Richard Gleeson to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, just over mid-wicket and Santner running back does so well to save two. A short of length delivery angling into off-stump, Shashank Singh punches and just clears Santner
Richard Gleeson to Shashank Singh, no run, a low full-toss outside off, driven straight to the fielder at cover-point, Shashank Singh has missed out there
Tushar Deshpande to Prabhsimran, SIX, Prabhsimran will continue to attack. He gives the charge and gets under the slower ball off-cutter, lofts and it's miles over long-on, went 89m

Tushar Deshpande to Prabhsimran, FOUR, again Prabhsimran is down the track, Tushar Deshpande did well to follow him, into the body but Prabhsimran adjusts and ramps the slower short ball over short third man, superb adjustment
Tushar Deshpande to Prabhsimran, no run, low full-toss on the stumps, clipped straight to the fielder at mid-on
Tushar Deshpande to Prabhsimran, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, drop and run in front of backward point for an easy run
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, FOUR, half-volley outside off, Shashank Singh gets forward and lofts over mid-off, one bounce over the ropes, Shashank Singh counter-attacking nicely
Tushar Deshpande to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Shashank Singh now shuffles across and clips the full ball to mid-wicket, takes on Simarjeet and the quick single is done

Powerplay summary -- Deshpande strikes twice to dent PBKS early -- Bairstow cleaned up for 7 (1.3) -- Rossouw gets clean bowled for 0 (1.6) -- Santner bowls two tight overs -- Prabhsimran cuts loose in final over of powerplay -- Shashank gets off to a brisk start
Ravindra Jadeja, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Jadeja to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, full ball on off, 94.8kph, Shashank looks to loft it down the ground but slices it off the outside half. It goes high in the air and falls wide of long-off
Jadeja to Shashank Singh, 1 run, 94kph length ball sliding into the pads, Shashank clips it through midwicket
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full ball down the leg-side, Prabhsimran paddles it to short fine
Jadeja to Shashank Singh, no run, defended down the pitch
Jadeja to Shashank Singh, 1 run, length ball darted in just outside off, 97kph, Shashank gets forward and punches to long-off
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, FOUR, brilliant shot! 88kph full ball fired in around leg stump, Prabhsimran backs away to the leg-side, makes enough room and hammers it through extra cover
Mitchell Santner [2.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack
Santner to Shashank Singh, no run, 94kph length ball on off, Shashank hangs back and punches to cover
Santner to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flat on off, 105.6kph, and Shashank punches it to long-on
Santner to Prabhsimran, no run, length ball darted in on off, Prabhsimran hangs back and defends
Santner to Prabhsimran, 1 run, Prabhsimran more watchful against Santner than against others. Length ball on off, he hangs back and punches to long-on
Santner to Shashank Singh, FOUR, too full from Santner and he gets hammered! Right in the slot on off stump, Shashank goes straight and drills it over the bowler's head
Santner to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Santner to Shashank Singh, out Caught by Simarjeet Singh!! Santner makes a slight adjustment from the previous delivery as he pulls his length back a touch. Shashank goes after this one as well, looking for the same straight hit down the ground. However, the ball dips and pitches further away than he expects. He miscues it off the inside half and holes out at long-on. Shashank Singh c Simarjeet Singh b Santner 27(20) [4s-4]
Dhoni went up to Jadeja for a quick chat after that dismissal
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, 1 run, drifting into the pads, flicked through midwicket
Jadeja to Sam Curran, 1 run, flat on middle and leg, Curran punches it to long-on
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, clipped off the pads through square leg, and he's back for two
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full on off, Prabhsimran knocks it to long-on
Jadeja to Sam Curran, 1 run, full outside off, Curran gets forward and drives crisply to sweeper cover
Jadeja to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Prabhsimran, out Caught by (sub)Sameer Rizvi !! Prabhsimran throws his head back in disappointment as he finds the fielder at long-off! He was looking to go much wider of that man. Full ball around leg stump, he backs away looking to go inside out over extra cover but doesn't quite get hold of it properly. Goes much straighter than he wants and it's a simple catch for the substitute fielder. Jadeja points towards Dhoni immediately after the catch is taken. Prabhsimran c (sub)Sameer Rizvi b Jadeja 30(23) [4s-2 6s-2]
Timeout!
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Simarjeet Singh, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, no run, short of length on off, Curran mistimes the pull to midwicket
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, no run, back of a length outside off, Curran opens the face and punches it to backward point
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, 1 run, short of length into the body, Curran is hurried on the pull and miscues it in the air in front of fine leg
Simarjeet Singh to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Simarjeet Singh to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Dhoni!! Jitesh gone for a golden duck and PBKS in big trouble now! Short of length outside off, good pace and bounce, and it gets big on Jitesh as he looks to cut. Takes a healthy edge through to Dhoni who makes no mistake to his right. Jitesh Sharma c Dhoni b Simarjeet Singh 0(1)
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Simarjeet Singh to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, what was that from Ashutosh?! Back of a length on middle, around waist height, and he almost reacts as if he didn't see the ball at all. Brings the bat down at an awkward angle and somehow gets it off the bat-handle through square leg
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, 2 runs, short of length into the body, Curran is rushed on the pull and miscues it in the air wide of long-on. Back for two runs
Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, full on off, pushed back to Jadeja
Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, full ball just outside off, Ashutosh gets forward and pushes to cover
Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, fired in full on off, Ashutosh gets forward and pushes to long-off

Jadeja to Sam Curran, no run, appeal for LBW but this seems to have pitched outside leg. Dhoni isn't keen on the review, so Ruturaj obviously doesn't take it. Length ball darted in from round the wicket, straightens a touch to beat the inside edge in defence and hits the front pad. Pitching well outside leg
Jadeja to Sam Curran, 1 run, slightly short outside off, Curran cuts to sweeper cover
Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, squeezed away through cover for another single. Just three off the over
Lowest top-order batting averages in IPL 2024 24.37 - PBKS 25.62 - MI 28.38 - GT 29.33 - DC
Simarjeet Singh's last appearance in competitive cricket was back in December 2022 (Ranji Trophy 2022/23).

Simarjeet Singh to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, Ashutosh is in pain after being struck on the body! Back of a length on middle, 141kph, skids through sharply and strikes him on the right hip as he misses the pull
Simarjeet Singh to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, Simarjeet is steaming in here! 145kph back of a length delivery around off, Ashutosh looks to run it towards deep third but it nips in and cuts him in half
Simarjeet Singh to Ashutosh Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, length ball angled in around leg, Ashutosh looks for a pick-up shot but is hit on the thigh
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, no run, back of a length outside off, Curran hangs back and dabs it to backward point. Was looking to get it a bit finer than that for a single
Simarjeet Singh to Sam Curran, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Curran shuffles across and tucks it through square leg

Simarjeet Singh to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, Moeen drops a sitter and then seems to suggest he lost it in the background! Short of length at the body, Ashutosh is rushed on the pull, gets it high on the bat and it loops to midwicket. Was an absolute dolly
Jadeja to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Sam Curran, out Caught by Santner!! Punjab Kings are falling apart! Length ball fired in outside off, Curran flat-bats it hard down the ground, doesn't get much elevation and it's straight to Santner at long-off. Not much batting left for the hosts now. Sam Curran c Santner b Jadeja 7(11)
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, driven through the covers
Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Jadeja to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Simarjeet Singh!! Third wicket for Jadeja, second of the over, and PBKS are now seven down! Length ball fired in outside off, Ashutosh looks to slog but there's a bit of grip and turn. It balloons off a thick edge and Simarjeet gobbles it comfortably at short third. Ashutosh Sharma c Simarjeet Singh b Jadeja 3(10)
Harshal Patel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Jadeja to Harshal Patel, no run, length ball just outside off, slightly slower through the air, draws Harshal forward in defence and turns it away past the outside edge
Jadeja to Harshal Patel, no run, defended
Jadeja to Harshal Patel, 1 run, full on off, Harshal pushes it to long-off. Jadeja finishes with 3/20!
Richard Gleeson [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, no run, good length on middle and leg, skids through sharply as Harshal is caught in the crease in defence. An inside-edge onto pad saves him
Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, no run, short of length delivery just outside off, Harshal dabs it to backward point
Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, no run, short of length outside off, Harshal looks to cut and is beaten
Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, no run, full delivery on off, driven firmly to mid-off

Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, no run, back of a length on middle, Harshal looks to defend on the back foot but is squared up by some away movement. It nips away past the edge and bounces over the stumps
Richard Gleeson to Harshal Patel, 1 run, good length outside off, Harshal throws his bat at it and slaps it to deep point
Simarjeet Singh [2.0-0-5-1] is back into the attack
Simarjeet Singh to Harshal Patel, no run, short of length outside off, Harshal slashes hard but is beaten
Simarjeet Singh to Harshal Patel, SIX, short of length outside off, Harshal walks across the stumps and scoops it all the way over fine leg
Simarjeet Singh to Harshal Patel, FOUR, now goes the other side, and beats deep third! Short of length outside off, Harshal leans back and ramps it fine
Simarjeet Singh to Harshal Patel, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Simarjeet Singh to Harshal Patel, out Caught by (sub)Sameer Rizvi !! Big slog from Harshal, miscues it completely, and Rizvi completes a good catch running around the square leg umpire. It's a good length ball outside off, and it goes high in the air off a thick edge. Rizvi had to be sharp there. Harshal Patel c (sub)Sameer Rizvi b Simarjeet Singh 12(13) [4s-1 6s-1]
Rahul Chahar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Simarjeet Singh to Rahul Chahar, 1 run, 140.6kph full toss on middle, Chahar shuffles across and flicks to deep square leg
Simarjeet Singh to Harpreet Brar, no run, sharp bouncer around the head, Brar ducks under it and evades

Summary (Overs 7-15) > Shashank holes out looking to up the ante > Jadeja gets a set Prabhsimran in the 9th over > Simarjeet gets Jitesh for a golden duck > Curran and Ashutosh fall to Jadeja in the same over > PBKS slip from 62/2 to 78/7 > Harshal becomes the 8th casualty after falling to Simarjeet
Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, no run, back of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point
Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, no run, 144kph good length ball outside off, Chahar swings and misses
Simarjeet shaking his head for some reason at the boundary
Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, FOUR, back of a length outside off, Chahar swings hard, gets a thick edge and it flies past Dhoni
Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, FOUR, now he makes proper contact and gets four more! 146kph full ball around off, Chahar clears the front leg and creams it over mid-off
Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, no run, banged in short outside off at 140kph, Chahar slashes hard but is beaten

Richard Gleeson to Rahul Chahar, SIX, short of length into the body, Chahar swivels across, looks to pull and gets enough to clear fine leg. He's having fun out there after an excellent outing with the ball earlier
Timeout!
Tushar Deshpande [3.0-0-28-2] is back into the attack
Tushar Deshpande to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, short of length outside off, Brar flat-bats it to mid-off
Tushar Deshpande to Rahul Chahar, 1 run, good length on off, slower one, Chahar hangs back and taps it in front of backward point

Tushar Deshpande to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, short of length outside off, Brar opens the face and steers it nicely to the left of deep third. The fielder there is placed quite fine and it beats him comfortably to his left
Tushar Deshpande to Harpreet Brar, no run, sharp bouncer over the shoulders, Brar looks to pull but is beaten
Tushar Deshpande to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, slower length ball wide of off, Brar reaches out and mistimes it off the toe-end to long-off
Tushar Deshpande to Rahul Chahar, no run, full on middle and leg, slower one, Chahar looks to slog but it turns in and hits the back leg. Might've been an inside edge involved too
Shardul Thakur, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Thakur to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, back of a length outside off, slower one, sits up nicely for Brar and he slaps it through extra cover
Thakur to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, good length outside off, Brar reaches out and punches it to sweeper cover
Thakur to Rahul Chahar, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Thakur to Rahul Chahar, out Bowled!! Chahar goes a long way across the stumps, Thakur keeps it straight and manages to hit off stump. He was looking to play the scoop but got nowhere near it. Rahul Chahar b Thakur 16(10) [4s-2 6s-1]
Kagiso Rabada, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Thakur to Rabada, 1 run, slower ball floated up outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Thakur to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, full and very wide, slower one, Brar throws himself at it as he reaches out and drives one-handed to sweeper cover
Thakur to Rabada, wide, slower ball that's very wide outside off, left alone
Thakur to Rabada, 1 run, short of length delivery just outside off, Rabada pulls well and it goes on the bounce to long-on
Richard Gleeson [3.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack
Richard Gleeson to Rabada, wide, full and wide, slower ball, Rabada leaves it alone

Richard Gleeson to Rabada, no run, another wide one outside off, Rabada leaves it again and it's called wide again. Dhoni, though, immediately asks Ruturaj to go for the review. Rabada had moved across the stumps this time, so third umpire reckons it's not a wide
Richard Gleeson to Rabada, 1 run, low full toss, driven to long-off
Richard Gleeson to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, overpitched on middle, Brar flicks to long-on
Richard Gleeson to Rabada, 1 run, driven back hard down the pitch and it hits the umpire. He looks alright
Richard Gleeson to Harpreet Brar, 1 run
Richard Gleeson to Rabada, SIX, short of length on off, slower ball, sits up for Rabada who nails the pull over midwicket
Thakur to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, yorker on off, Brar squeezes it to long-off
Thakur to Rabada, no run, slower ball wide of off, Rabada swings and misses
Thakur to Rabada, leg byes, FOUR, full ball just outside leg, Rabada looks to swipe across the line, gets beaten on the inside edge but it clips the back pad and runs away fine for four
Thakur to Rabada, no run, short of length delivery just outside off, Rabada goes for a big pull shot but is beaten
Thakur to Rabada, 1 run, full toss outside off, Rabada reaches out and slices it over extra cover. It falls short of the fielder in the deep

Thakur to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, banged in short on off, Brar looks to pull but miscues it in the air. It falls well short of deep square leg and they amble across for a single. CSK bounce back from the defeat at Chepauk to win the reverse fixture here in Dharamsala

19:07 Local Time, 13:37 GMT, 19:07 IST: CSK have defended their total with ease. You wondered how good their score of 167 was at the halfway stage, but Punjab Kings didn't even get close against some good bowling on a slow pitch. Deshpande was on fire in the powerplay, knocking over Bairstow and Rossouw in the same over while Santner gave nothing away from the other end. CSK have been reluctant to start with spin in the powerplay, but the introduction of Santner today really gave them an added dimension. Punjab Kings did look in with a shot when Prabhsimran and Shashank had a brisk partnership of 53 for the third wicket. Things were evenly poised at that stage. But Jadeja came to the party and bowled a spell of 3/20 to turn the game completely in favour of CSK. Simarjeet Singh was impressive as well with his pace through those middle overs, making it a clinical performance with the ball from the visitors.

Sam Curran | PBKS Captain: Thought we bowled really well. Rahul Chahar and Harshal bowled really well, was pretty happy at the halfway point but unfortunately it wasn’t to be. The wicket was probably slower than we thought, we expected a little more pace and bounce, it was pretty similar throughout the game. Couple of days off and we go against RCB in a few days time so we need to move on and stay headstrong.

Tushar Deshpande: I'm very happy today as it was a low-scoring game in terms of the matches going on. This was the game we wanted to win badly. It was bad luck last game, I tried my best to play that one, but couldn't. It was a crunch game for us and to start well was very important. Dharamsala at high altitude the ball does something and my job at the front was to take wickets and it went well today. It was a bit slow, the pitch was quite stopping a bit. If you hit the length hard, it was not easy to hit the horizontal bat shots so we just backed our length and kept it simple. Just tried to hit the top of off with the new-ball.

PBKS had defeated CSK in each of the last five head-to-head games, which now remains the joint-longest winning streak for any team against CSK alongside MI’s five straight wins across the 2018 and 2019 editions. \nCSK’s last win over PBKS came during the IPL 2021 first leg (by 6 wickets at the Wankhede Stadium, Mumbai).
PBKS in home games IPL 2023: 7 matches, 1 win, 6 defeats IPL 2024: 6 matches, 1 win, 5 defeats Every other team has won at least four matches at home across the two editions.
Both wicketkeepers dismissed for a duck in an IPL game RR vs MI, Jaipur, 2010 MI vs RR, Mumbai WS, 2012 MI vs SRH, Mumbai WS, 2018 GT vs DC, Ahmedabad, 2023 PBKS vs CSK, Dharamsala, 2024
Double of 40-plus runs & 3 wickets in an IPL game most often 3 - Shane Watson 3 - Yuvraj Singh 3 - Ravindra Jadeja 2 - Andre Russell
Most POTM awards for CSK in the IPL 16 - Ravindra Jadeja 15 - MS Dhoni 12 - Suresh Raina 11 - Ruturaj Gaikwad 10 - Michael Hussey
Stats by Roshan Gede

Ruturaj, CSK captain: Everyone believed the wicket was slow. Even low bounce. Just that the start we got, we were thinking of pushing till 180-200. After losing wickets, thought 160-170 was a good score. Don't know what he's doing, but even in preseason he was clicking 150kph (on Simarjeet). He didn't get too much chances, but it's never too late. Were thinking of going with impact batter, but then we thought the batter will give 10-15 runs, but he could give 2-3 wickets. Some of the guys were struggling with flu. Weren't even sure till the morning who's playing or not. To get the win, really happy with that.

Jadeja, POTM: Was a day game so the wicket was slow. It was expected to be slow because it was quite warm. Wanted to build a partnership of 30-40 so that we have a platform for the end. The bowlers bowled well. Always looks a flat wicket in powerplay. But as the ball gets older, it doesn't come on very well. When you're playing at a new venue, you don't have an idea of how the pitch will be. Felt we were 15-20 short. My role is to build a partnership if we lose early wickets.

Punjab Kings may no longer have their fate in their own hands after this defeat. CSK, meanwhile, have gone up to third. Another crucial game is underway already in Lucknow where LSG are taking on KKR. Do join us there. This is Sagar Chawla signing off on behalf of Harish and Anurag Hegde. Goodbye!
